boolean setAttributes(java.lang.String operatorId,
                                  java.lang.String customCategoryName,
                                  java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> customAttributeNameAndValues,
                                  java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> standardAttributeNameAndValues)
                           throws PresenceException
        Deprecated. To set the custom attributes use setAttributes(String, ClipboardPage)
        Modifies presence record for the operator specified
        Parameters:
        operatorId - : operator whose presence record should be modified.
        customCategoryName - : category of custom attributes
        customAttributeNameAndValues - : map of name and values for attributes under above category. If the category or attribute do not exist in a presence record, new one is created.
        standardAttributeNameAndValues - : map of name and values for attributes under standard category. If the standard attribute does not exist or is only readable call , then this input is considered as invalid input.
        Returns:
        true indicates that presence record is successfully updated.
        Throws:
        PresenceException - indicates invalid input or an error

      • setAttributes

        boolean setAttributes(java.lang.String operatorId,
                      ClipboardPage customAttributesPage)
               throws PresenceException
        Updates the custom attributes of given operator. Custom category is derived from pxObjClass of given Custom Attributes clipboard page. While updating custom attributes, given custom attributes page is merged with the existing custom attributes.

        Warning: Clipboard merge operation does not support merging of PageList properties, it is advised not to use PageList properties in custom attributes.

        Parameters:
        operatorId - Operator Id to which custom attributes needs to be updated
        customAttributesPage - ClipboardPage contains custom attributes with pxObjClass property populated
        Returns:
        boolean Returns true if the operation is successful false otherwise
        Throws:
        PresenceException - Throws PresenceException in case of any mis configurations and runtime issues

      • queryPresence

        java.util.List<PresenceRecord> queryPresence(java.lang.String queryString,
                                             java.util.List<PresenceQueryClause> queryClauses,
                                             java.lang.String categoryToReturn)
                                      throws PresenceException
        API queries presence information and returns matching presence records
        Parameters:
        categoryToReturn - Category of attributes to be returned for matching records. This should match with category if mentioned in the conditions array.
        queryString - This expression joins PresenceQueryClauses mentioned in queryClauses parameter using predefined tokens: AND, OR, ), (, space
        Each query clause is identified using queryclauseIdentifiers mentioned in PresenceQueryClause.
        PresenceException is thrown for invalid queryString.
        queryClauses - array of PresenceQueryClause.
        Returns:
        PresenceRecord[] returns array of matching records. Empty array indicates zero records.
        Throws:
        PresenceException - indicates invalid input or an error
